Diagnosis.
Female (
Fig. 52
). Frons mainly yellowish brown, only darker brown around orbital setae (
Fig. 53
). Parafacial spots and orbital spots absent (
Fig. 54
); frons with pair of posterior orbital setae. Antennal scape yellowish brown, distinctly lighter than pedicel (
Fig. 54
). Fore tibia and basitarsus normal in both sexes. Thorax mainly black except yellow upper margin of pleuron. Scutellum with pair of apical scutellar setae. Wing infumated, usually with darker anterior portion and apex (
Fig. 52
). Male similar to female in external characters except terminalia.

Male terminalia: Sternum 5 divided into two subtriangular sclerites (
Fig. 55
). Cercus elongated, rod-like (
Fig. 56
). Surstylus similar to that of 

S. plumbella

, sickle-like in caudal view (
Fig. 56–57
). Hypandrium with a deep cleft at outer edge (
Fig. 58
). Cochleate vesicle present (
Fig. 56–57
). Aedeagus and apodemes as shown in 
Figs. 59–60
.
